data.title: Bigg Boss contestant will bash up Salman in 'Mental'
data.meta_description: Bigg Boss 6 has worked wonders for Santosh Shukla. He will be seen bashing up Salman Khan in Sohail Khan's film 'Mental', in which Santosh plays the negative role.
data.text:
Abhishek Bachchan Responds to Divorce Speculation Amid Viral Fake Video: Reports

Abhishek Bachchan has finally addressed the rumors about a split with his wife, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan. During a recent interview, he displayed his wedding ring and expressed his frustration over the speculation, while acknowledging that such rumours are part of celebrity life. Abhishek stated, 'I am still married. I don't have anything to say to you all about that. You all have blown the entire thing out of proportion, sadly. I understand why you do it; you have to file some stories. It's okay, we're celebrities, we have to take it.' The rumours started when Abhishek and Aishwarya attended separate events at the Ambani wedding, and were further fueled by Abhishek’s like on a post about divorce cases.

2236 views | 20 hours ago

Rupali Ganguly Calls for Global Action to Protect Minorities in Bangladesh

Rupali Ganguly recently spoke out about the plight of minorities in Bangladesh, urging global voices to support the helpless amid escalating protests. The 'Anupamaa' actress expressed her anguish on X, emphasizing her father's Bangladeshi roots. Her post included hashtags such as 'All Eyes on Bangladesh' and 'All Eyes on Bangladeshi Hindu.' She wrote, “The stories of persecution of Hindus in Bangladesh have left me in a state of anguish. Having my father’s roots in present-day Bangladesh, it scares me to think of the constant atrocities and violence the minorities are being subjected to. This is the time for every human being throughout the world to stand up and raise our voice for the protection of the helpless and vulnerable minorities in Bangladesh.' In addition, Sonu Sood had previously shared a heart-wrenching video of a Bangladeshi woman crying for help. On August 5, Sheikh Hasina resigned as Bangladesh's Prime Minister and flew to India. During the protests, actor Shanto Khan and his father, producer Selim Khan, were brutally killed.

557 views | 4 days ago

Sonu Sood Calls for Immediate Action to Bring Indians Home from Crisis-Hit Bangladesh

After former Bangladesh Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina fled the country on a military aircraft, Sonu Sood called on both the government and citizens to assist in evacuating Indians from violence-hit Bangladesh. He shared a video of a Bangladeshi Hindu woman crying over the dire situation, emphasising the urgency of bringing all Indians back from the country. In response, Air India conducted a special flight that successfully evacuated over 200 people from Dhaka. The crisis has also drawn concern from celebrities such as Sonam Kapoor and Kangana Ranaut, who have voiced their support for the evacuation efforts. On the work front, Sonu Sood will next be seen in the film Fateh.
